.TH "alter" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
alter \- modify the properties of the domain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]domain.alter(<options>)\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDomain
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to modify the properties of the domain.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
User must ensure that the group does not contain any data before deletiong a
replication group, otherwise the operation will fail.
.IP \[bu] 2
Changing "AutoSplit" will not affect the existing collection and collection
space.
.RE
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
options ( \f[I]object, required\f[] )
.PP
The properties of the domain can be modified through the options parameter:
.IP \[bu] 2
Groups ( \f[I]string/array\f[] ): All replication groups contained in the
domain.
.PP
Format: \f[C]Groups:\ [\[aq]group1\[aq],\ \[aq]group2\[aq]]\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
AutoSplit ( \f[I]boolean\f[] ): Whether the domain is automatically split.
.PP
Format: \f[C]AutoSplit:\ true|false\f[]
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
When the function executes successfully, there is no return value.
.PP
When the function fails, an exception will be thrown and an error message will
be printed.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
